The paper deals with deep learning techniques and generative models for increasing the training set in a classification framework when data is scarce. This suggests that the paper is likely to belong to the sub-categories of machine learning (cs.LG), artificial intelligence (cs.AI), computer vision (cs.CV), neural and evolutionary computing (cs.NE), and computational linguistics (cs.CL). However, since the paper focuses on deep learning and generative models, cs.LG and cs.AI are the most likely sub-categories.
